Transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs) are fatal neurodegenerative diseases that include Creutzfeldt to Jakob disease (CJD), Gerstmann to Straussler to Scheinker syndrome and fatal familial insomnia in humans, scrapie in sheep and goats and bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) (Collinge, 2001). They are characterized by the accumulation of the abnormal scrapie isoform of the prion protein (PrPSc) in the brain
